# DryDocs — Plan v3 (delta on v2)

This is a **delta** on `drydocs_plan.md` (v2). v2 still applies as the base — same ontology stack (DPROD → DCAT → PROV-O / PROV-DM → OpenLineage → DQV → SWO → ORG), same TDQ pipeline, same KGoT seam. v3 adds the corporate scaffolding, two-port Application pattern, scheduler-as-requirement, channel typology, support team derivation, Control-M server mesh, BMC condition-event dependency model, versioning, and Oracle refresh cadence.

Read v2 first; v3 sections below either **add to**, **amend**, or **resolve open questions in** specific v2 sections.

---

## §A. Goal — restated (amends v2 §1)

**Primary use case**: production support inventory. Each support team covers 8–15 business applications and there is no single source of truth for jobs, datasets, or SLAs. This graph is that source of truth.

**Secondary lens**: data products. The DPROD/DCAT framing from v2 stays — it's how teams want to *view* what they support, not the destination.

This reordering matters because it changes which queries are first-class (support-team-by-app, all-jobs-for-app, lineage-from-failed-job-to-incident-queue) and what the Streamlit nav prioritizes.

