## §D. Scheduler-as-requirement (new — amends v2 §4.5 scheduler treatment)

Phase 1 ingests Control-M only. But `:Application` (or `:BatchProcessing`) declares which orchestrators it depends on, even when not yet ingested:

```
:BatchProcessing -[:REQUIRES_SCHEDULER]-> :SchedulerKind {name:"ControlM"|"Autosys"|"Airflow"}
```

`:SchedulerKind` is a small placeholder vocabulary (4–5 nodes), not a runtime instance. A separate `:Scheduler {kind:"ControlM", instance:"prod-east"}` represents an actual deployed scheduler — only Control-M instances exist in phase 1.

Streamlit "Application" page shows the kinds an app requires (Control-M, Autosys, Airflow) so support teams know what platforms they're on the hook for, even if Autosys/Airflow ingestion is phase 2+.

