## §E. Channel typology (new — slots into v2 §4.x)

`:Channel` is a node type. Subtypes by origin:

```
:Channel:SftpChannel       — files arriving via SFTP from another app or vendor
:Channel:UserSftpChannel   — files uploaded by a human user
:Channel:UploadChannel     — UI-driven file upload
:Channel:ApiChannel        — file produced by an API call (often by a predecessor job)
:Channel:UpstreamJobChannel — file produced by another Control-M job upstream
```

Why this matters: jobs labeled `FW` (file watcher) don't tell you the *origin* of the file. Modeling channels makes the discrepancy queryable — "show me all FW jobs whose file actually came from a user SFTP, not an upstream system" surfaces hidden dependencies.

Edges:

```
:DataFile -[:ARRIVED_VIA]-> :Channel
:Channel  -[:ORIGINATES_FROM]-> :Application | :Vendor | :Person | :Job
```

The TDQ pipeline (v2 §4.4) is unchanged — the channel sits *upstream* of the data file arrival; the data file + control file pair → TDQ check still works the same way.

