## §I. Versioning + Oracle refresh cadence (new — combines answers to Q1 & Q6)

Tracking rule: **anything at or above `:Application` versions on update**. Below `:Application` (BatchProcessing children: jobs, folders, files, etc.) does *not* version — those refresh in place.

Implementation:

```
(:Application)-[:HAS_VERSION {version_id, valid_from, valid_to, source}]->(:ApplicationSnapshot)
```

Snapshots store the relationship state as of `valid_from`. New snapshot is created when:
- L2 operate manager changes
- Dev team mapping changes
- Product catalog reassignment (Product → Application)
- Business segment reassignment (only triggers if effective-dating crossed)

Same pattern applies to `:Product`, `:ProductLine`, `:CatalogLOB`, `:BusinessSegment`. Snapshot tables intentionally stay light — they hold relationship deltas, not the full subgraph.

**Oracle source loaders** (refresh cadence):

| Oracle source | Loader | Cadence | Versions on change? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Product catalog | `catalog_*.py` | Weekly or monthly | Yes (at/above Application) |
| **SEAL** application registry | `seal_applications.py` | Weekly | Yes — properties + 5 SEAL Memberships |
| **PAT** product/app contacts | `pat_applications.py` | Weekly | Yes — Agility Lead, Software Engineer, Product Contact |
| Dev teams | `dev_teams.py` | Weekly | Yes |
| BMC `DEF_JOB`, `DEF_TABLES`, `DEF_LINKI_P`, `DEF_LINKO_P` | `controlm_*.py` | Daily | No (refresh in place) |
| HR org hierarchy | `org_hierarchy.py` | Weekly | Yes (`:MANAGES` chain feeds support-team derivation) |
| ServiceNow groups | `servicenow_groups.py` | Weekly | Yes |

Connection: `oracledb` driver (formerly `cx_Oracle`). Add to deps. Read-only Oracle creds in `.env`.

