## §L. Streamlit amendments (amends v2 §8)

New / changed pages:

- **Application Inventory** (new, primary page): paginated/searchable list of 1991 apps; filters by BusinessSegment / CatalogLOB / ProductLine / SchedulerKind / **status** (BUILD/OPERATE/RETIRED) / **risk_level** / **sox_governed**. Click → Application Detail.
- **Application Detail** (new): card with corporate hierarchy crumb (Segment > LOB > ProductLine > Product > App); SEAL properties (deployment module, data retention, risk level, SOX, status); the two ports; **all SEAL Memberships** (App Owner, Data Owner, L2 Operate Manager, Risk Manager, CTO) and **all PAT Memberships** (Agility Lead, Software Engineers, inherited Product Contact); dev team(s); derived support team; required schedulers; version history (snapshots).
- **Support Team by App** (new, headline derived view): the §F.4 Cypher rendered as a sortable table; the page support engineers will live in.
- **Reconciliation Issues** (new — covers §F.5): apps missing SEAL L2 Operate Manager; SEAL App Owner ↔ PAT Software Engineer mismatches; PAT Product Contact ↔ child-app CTO mismatches; SEAL OPERATE-status apps with no PAT entry. Clickable rows jump to Application Detail.
- **Channel Onramps** (new): every `:Channel`, what it feeds, which apps depend on it. Highlights FW jobs whose channel origin disagrees with the assumed upstream.
- **Control-M Job Graph** (changed): condition-event view (Job → Condition → Job) with toggle to show derived `:DEPENDS_ON` only. Folder filter, server filter.
- **Version History** (new): timeline of ApplicationSnapshot, ProductSnapshot, CatalogLOBSnapshot deltas — answers "what changed last week."
- **Pipeline Explorer** (changed): unchanged shape, but now starts from BatchProcessing of an app, not from a Folder.
- **Data Quality Scoreboard, Arrivals & TDQ, Recent Runs, Risks, Ontology Coverage** — unchanged from v2.

Auth: read-only Neo4j user. App search uses the `application_seal` constraint as a fast lookup.

